This is a serious and a most alarming
movement
,
Mr. Goldencalf, observed Sir Joseph, and
calls for union and cordiality among the holders
of property. Should these damnable opinions get
fairly abroad among the people, what would
become
of us?I ask, Mr. Goldencalf, what would
become of us?
I agree with you, Sir Joseph, it is very
alarming
!frightfully
alarming!
We shall have Agrarian laws, sir.Your
money
,
